Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I have a Garmin RV 785 GPS for my motorcoach. The Supmay 10-inch GPS case holds my unit with room to spare. It has two compartments, one for the GPS and one for the long cords I use to mount the GPS on my dash. This allows me to store the GPS unit safely in the overhead compartment of the RV keeping from getting scratched or possibly losing my cords and adapter. The outer shell seems to be ridged enough to protect the unit. I should be able to carry the Tire Pressure Monitor in the case as well giving this case an added value for me.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Case for Multiple Uses
reviews.reviewText: This is a nice large case for just about any type of equipment you might need to store. I use it for something other than the Garmin GPS device. It's built of quality materials and protects electronic equipment very well. It has a cushion flap in the middle that allows you to store cables and other accessories. The size of the case is compatible with many different types of electronics equipment and works well for long- or short-term storage. Great case!
